# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# xray_chest — Chest X-Ray
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

[[screens]]
id = "xray_chest"
name = "Chest X-Ray"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 0
  col = 0
  label = "Normal"
  action = "text"
  content = """PA and lateral chest radiographs were obtained.

Lungs are clear without focal consolidation, pneumothorax, or pleural
effusion. Cardiomediastinal silhouette is normal. No pulmonary edema.
Costophrenic angles are sharp. Trachea is midline. Osseous structures
and soft tissues are unremarkable.

IMPRESSION: Normal chest radiograph."""
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 0
  col = 1
  label = "Effusion R"
  action = "text"
  content = """PA and lateral chest radiographs.

Blunting of the right costophrenic angle with a meniscoid opacity
tracking up the lateral chest wall, consistent with right pleural
effusion. Left lung is clear. Cardiomediastinal silhouette is normal.

IMPRESSION: Right pleural effusion. US correlation recommended."""
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 0
  col = 2
  label = "Effusion L"
  action = "text"
  content = """PA and lateral chest radiographs.

Blunting of the left costophrenic angle with a meniscoid opacity
tracking up the lateral chest wall, consistent with left pleural
effusion. Right lung is clear. Cardiomediastinal silhouette is normal.

IMPRESSION: Left pleural effusion. US correlation recommended."""
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 0
  col = 3
  label = "Pneumothorax"
  action = "text"
  content = """PA and lateral chest radiographs.

Visible visceral pleural line in the right hemithorax with absence of
lung markings peripheral to this line, consistent with right-sided
pneumothorax (estimated 30%). No mediastinal shift. Left lung is clear.

IMPRESSION: Right pneumothorax. Clinical correlation recommended."""
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 0
  col = 4
  label = "Pneumonia"
  action = "text"
  content = """PA and lateral chest radiographs.

Focal airspace opacity in the right lower lobe with air bronchograms,
consistent with consolidation. No pleural effusion. Left lung is clear.
Cardiomediastinal silhouette is normal.

IMPRESSION: RLL consolidation, suggestive of pneumonia."""
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 0
  col = 5
  label = "CHF/Edema"
  action = "text"
  content = """PA and lateral chest radiographs.

Cardiomegaly (CTR > 0.5). Bilateral perihilar and interstitial opacities
with Kerley B lines, consistent with pulmonary edema. Small bilateral
pleural effusions. Cephalization of pulmonary vasculature.

IMPRESSION: CHF with pulmonary edema. Correlate with BNP."""
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 1
  col = 0
  label = "Atelectasis"
  action = "text"
  content = """PA and lateral chest radiographs.

Linear bandlike opacity in the left lung base with volume loss
(ipsilateral diaphragmatic elevation and mediastinal shift),
consistent with platelike atelectasis. No consolidation or effusion.

IMPRESSION: Left basilar platelike atelectasis."""
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 1
  col = 1
  label = "Nodule"
  action = "text"
  content = """PA and lateral chest radiographs.

Solitary well-circumscribed nodular opacity measuring ~8 mm in the
right upper lobe. No calcification. No other nodules. Remainder of
lungs is clear.

IMPRESSION: Solitary pulmonary nodule, 8 mm, RUL. Comparison with
prior studies and CT recommended per Fleischner guidelines."""
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 1
  col = 2
  label = "Fibrosis"
  action = "text"
  content = """PA and lateral chest radiographs.

Bilateral reticular opacities with basal and subpleural predominance,
consistent with UIP pattern. Volume loss with diaphragmatic tenting.
No effusion or pneumothorax.

IMPRESSION: Bilateral pulmonary fibrosis with UIP pattern. HRCT
recommended. Correlate for CTD or hypersensitivity pneumonitis."""
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 4
  col = 0
  label = "SLine"
  action = "select_line"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 4
  col = 1
  label = "LStart"
  action = "line_start"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 4
  col = 2
  label = "LEnd"
  action = "line_end"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 4
  col = 3
  label = "Del"
  action = "delete"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 5
  col = 0
  label = "Back"
  action = "prev"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 5
  col = 1
  label = "Home"
  action = "home"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 5
  col = 2
  label = "SelAll"
  action = "select_all"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 5
  col = 3
  label = "Copy"
  action = "copy"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 5
  col = 4
  label = "Paste"
  action = "paste"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 5
  col = 5
  label = "Bksp"
  action = "backspace"

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# xray_abdomen — Abdomen X-Ray
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

[[screens]]
id = "xray_abdomen"
name = "Abdomen X-Ray"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 0
  col = 0
  label = "Normal"
  action = "text"
  content = """Supine and upright abdominal radiographs.

Normal bowel gas distribution. No obstruction, ileus, or free air.
No pathological calcifications or masses. Solid organs and bones
are unremarkable.

IMPRESSION: Normal abdominal series."""
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 0
  col = 1
  label = "Ileus"
  action = "text"
  content = """Supine and upright abdominal radiographs.

Diffuse gaseous distention of small and large bowel without transition
point, consistent with generalized adynamic ileus. No free air or
mechanical obstruction.

IMPRESSION: Generalized adynamic ileus. Correlate clinically."""
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 0
  col = 2
  label = "SBO"
  action = "text"
  content = """Supine and upright abdominal radiographs.

Multiple dilated small bowel loops with air-fluid levels on upright
view. Transition zone suggested in mid-abdomen. Paucity of colonic
gas distally.

IMPRESSION: Small bowel obstruction. CT abdomen/pelvis with IV
contrast recommended."""
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 0
  col = 3
  label = "Free Air"
  action = "text"
  content = """Supine and upright abdominal radiographs.

Linear lucency under the right hemidiaphragm on upright view,
consistent with free intraperitoneal air. No obstruction or ileus.

IMPRESSION: Pneumoperitoneum. Immediate surgical evaluation required."""
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 4
  col = 0
  label = "SLine"
  action = "select_line"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 4
  col = 1
  label = "LStart"
  action = "line_start"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 4
  col = 2
  label = "LEnd"
  action = "line_end"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 4
  col = 3
  label = "Del"
  action = "delete"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 5
  col = 0
  label = "Back"
  action = "prev"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 5
  col = 1
  label = "Home"
  action = "home"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 5
  col = 2
  label = "SelAll"
  action = "select_all"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 5
  col = 3
  label = "Copy"
  action = "copy"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 5
  col = 4
  label = "Paste"
  action = "paste"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 5
  col = 5
  label = "Bksp"
  action = "backspace"

