# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# xray_hand_pediatric — Pediatric Hand
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

[[screens]]
id = "xray_hand_pediatric"
name = "Pediatric Hand"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 0
  col = 0
  label = "Salter II"
  action = "text"
  content = """PA and lateral views of the right wrist (10-year-old).

Fracture through distal radial physis extending into metaphysis,
consistent with Salter-Harris type II. Minimal dorsal displacement
(< 3 mm). Epiphysis in normal position. Ulna intact.

IMPRESSION: SH-II distal radius fracture, minimally displaced.
Closed reduction and short-arm cast for 4-6 weeks."""
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 0
  col = 1
  label = "Torus"
  action = "text"
  content = """PA and lateral views of the left wrist (7-year-old).

Subtle buckling of dorsal cortex of distal radial metaphysis without
cortical disruption, consistent with torus (buckle) fracture. No
physeal involvement. Ulna normal.

IMPRESSION: Torus fracture of distal radius. Splint or cast for 3-4
weeks. Excellent prognosis."""
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 0
  col = 2
  label = "Greenstick"
  action = "text"
  content = """PA and lateral views of the right forearm (6-year-old).

Transverse fracture through radial mid-diaphysis with dorsal cortical
disruption but intact volar cortex — greenstick fracture. ~15 degrees
dorsal angulation. Ulna intact.

IMPRESSION: Greenstick fracture of radius with moderate angulation.
Closed reduction and long-arm cast for 6 weeks."""
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 4
  col = 0
  label = "SLine"
  action = "select_line"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 4
  col = 1
  label = "LStart"
  action = "line_start"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 4
  col = 2
  label = "LEnd"
  action = "line_end"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 4
  col = 3
  label = "Del"
  action = "delete"
