[[screens]]
id = "ct_chest_interstitial"
name = "ILD Patterns"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 0
  col = 0
  label = "UIP"
  action = "text"
  content = """HRCT of the chest.

Bilateral, basilar, subpleural predominant reticular opacity with
honeycombing and traction bronchiectasis, consistent with UIP pattern.
No GGO to suggest alternative diagnosis. Mild lower lobe volume loss.

IMPRESSION: UIP pattern on HRCT. Correlate for IPF vs CTD-ILD.
Multidisciplinary discussion recommended."""
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 0
  col = 1
  label = "NSIP"
  action = "text"
  content = """HRCT of the chest.

Bilateral, symmetric, lower-lobe predominant GGO with fine reticulation
and traction bronchiectasis. Relative subpleural sparing favoring NSIP
pattern. No honeycombing.

IMPRESSION: NSIP pattern on HRCT. Consider CTD-associated ILD. PFTs
and rheumatology evaluation recommended."""
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 4
  col = 0
  label = "SLine"
  action = "select_line"
