name = "Aortic Syndrome"
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 0
  col = 0
  label = "Dissect. A"
  action = "text"
  content = """CT angiography of chest, abdomen, and pelvis.

Intimal flap in ascending aorta originating just above aortic root
and extending into descending thoracic aorta (Stanford type A). True
lumen smaller than false lumen. Mild AR and small pericardial effusion.
Coronary ostia patent. No abdominal extension.

IMPRESSION: Stanford type A aortic dissection with pericardial
effusion. Surgical emergency — immediate CT surgery consultation."""
  [[screens.buttons]]
  row = 0
  col = 1
  label = "Dissect. B"
  action = "text"
  content = """CT angiography of chest, abdomen, and pelvis.

Intimal flap in descending thoracic aorta beginning distal to left
subclavian artery and extending to renal arteries (Stanford type B).
Involves origin of SMA. No rupture or malperfusion.

IMPRESSION: Stanford type B dissection involving SMA origin. Vascular
surgery for BP management and possible TEVAR."""
